Transurban's operating assets are primarily Iong-Iife intangible assets (concession assets), representing the provision by Government entities for the right to toll customers for the use of the assets. Concession assets represent 76 per cent of the total assets of the Group. The total duration of the concessions typically range from approximately 30 to 80 years, and for accounting purposes the carrying values are amortised on a straight line basis over the duration of the concession.
